File: The interns will be deployed to hospitals across the country. JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department has announced that 2,369 interns will join the health workforce. The country will soon receive 650 graduates from the Nelson Mandela Fidel Castro Cuba medical programme. READ: Health workers are burning out: SAMA The interns will be deployed to hospitals across the country. In April, over 200 Cuban healthcare workers landed in South Africa to combat the coronavirus pandemic. The team -- made up of doctors and specialists -- was deployed across the country.